<div class="container container-main">
    <div class="row">

        <div class="col-12">
            <h1 class="title-text">@ViewBag.Subtitle</h1>
            <h2>CiCi Miniseries</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h5>
                The miniseries will be available through the publisher (that's me) until his stash runs out.
                I submitted to <a href="http://www.Comixology.com">Comixology</a> late 2016 and in January of 2017 they sent a rejection.
                Something about the PDF margins were off and I had NO idea how to fix those.
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h5>
                So it goes.  There a a few sites that have the preview (gray tone) issue and issue #2 on them, but I have yet to find issues #3 or #4.
                Is that even legal?  Has copyright run out?  At least it's getting the views (~14,000)
                I may try to build a reader on this site, or use a free version.  I'll look into it.
                Or maybe chop up the pages and try to animate them while scrolling (mostly for mobile).
                Not a huge fan of digital comics, but that's for YOU to decide.
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h5>
                This is a long and painful waiting game since the comic was accepted by Diamond Distributors back in 2002.  If you need single issues
                just shoot me an @Html.ActionLink("email", "Contact", "Home") and I'll get it to you.
            </h5>
        </div>

